## Background

The POS frontend (Vite + React) has a complete UI design with forms, tables, and pages for all business modules. However, all data is currently **hardcoded or stored only in local React state** â€” nothing is persisted to the database. The backend (Express + MongoDB + TypeScript) is fully set up with 16 modules, each having Controller â†’ Service â†’ Model â†’ Route architecture with Zod validation and JWT auth middleware.

**Goal**: Connect every frontend page to its corresponding backend API endpoint so that all CRUD operations (create, read, update, delete) persist to MongoDB via the backend.

